7. The pattern of incidence of diseases and behavioural patterns in the indexed family is given in Table 10a, Table 10b
(Fig. 1
). It showed a high prevalence of Parkinson’s disease (8%), schizophrenia (23%), neoplasms (20%), syndrome-X (33%), rheumatoid arthritis (16%) and epilepsy (6.6%). The psychological behavioural patterns of the family were as follows – creativity and high IQ (60%), hypersexual behaviour (60%), reduced appetite and eating behaviour (60%), insomnia and reduced sleep patterns (60%), increased tendency for spirituality (80%), increased tendency for addiction (50%) and less of bonding and affectionate behaviour (75%). Thirty per cent of the family members were left-handed (Fig. 1, Table 10a, Table 10b).
